EON AG,  Germany â€™s largest utility,
plans to raise 5.5 billion euros ($7.2 billion) selling gas grid
and waste-to-energy units as well a regional business in the
northwest of the country.  EON said today it has raised 9.5 billion euros out of a
planned 15 billion-euro divestment program. It said further sale
candidates are the Open Grid Europe gas pipeline unit, EON
Waste-to-Energy and EON Westfalen Weser. It expects to complete
the disposals by the end of 2013, according to a presentation
